de.unisiegen.tpml.core.typechecker
Interface TypeCheckerProofContext

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultTypeCheckerProofContext
public interface TypeCheckerProofContext

The proof context for the type checker. The proof context acts as an interface to the proof model for the type rules.

Version:
$Rev: 296 $
Author:
Benedikt Meurer
See Also:

Method Detail

addEquation

void addEquation(MonoType left,
                 MonoType right)
Adds a type equation to the list of type equations that serve as input for the unification algorithm.

Parameters:
left - the monomorphic type on the left side.
right - the monomorphic type on the right side.
See Also:
TypeEquation

addProofNode

void addProofNode(TypeCheckerProofNode node,
                  TypeEnvironment environment,
                  Expression expression,
                  MonoType type)
Adds a new child node below the node, to prove the type safety of the expression in the specified environment. The type is either a type variable or a concrete type, that is the expected type for the expression (used during the unification).

Parameters:
node - the parent node.
environment - the new TypeEnvironment for the child node.
expression - the expression for the child node.
type - the expected type for the expression.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the node is invalid for the proof model that is associated with this proof context.
NullPointerException - if any of the parameters is null.

getTypeForExpression

Type getTypeForExpression(Expression expression)
Returns the Type for the given expression if possible, i.e. (BOOL) if expression is an instance of BooleanConstant.

Parameters:
expression - an Expression.
Returns:
the Type for the expression.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if expression is not a simple expression, like a constant for which it is possible to determine the type out of the box.
NullPointerException - if expression is null.

instantiate

MonoType instantiate(Type type)
Instantiates the type using the context information. That said, if type is a PolyType the newTypeVariable() method is used to allocate new type variables for the quantified variables of the polymorphic type, while if type is a MonoType this method simply returns the type.

Parameters:
type - the Type to instantiate.
Returns:
the instantiated monomorphic type.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if type is null.
See Also:
MonoType, PolyType

newTypeVariable

TypeVariable newTypeVariable()
Allocates a new TypeVariable that is not already used in the type checker proof model associated with this type checker proof context.

Returns:
a new, unique TypeVariable.
